annotation.TEXT: So, where are those remaining Yoshi coins? There's nothing hidden beyond the goal, is there?
Okay, that's all six, and the goal is right here. But, you better believe that I'm coming back into this level again for Yoshi!
More Oil Drum Alley music? Or maybe it's gonna be Blackout Basement this time.
So, yeah! This level took a DKC gimmick and improved on it! Very well done!
Oh, what's this? And why do I wish I'd hit the yellow switch by this point? Okay, don't panic. Just work out the timing here...
This part looks tricky... (A lot of parts look tricky lately!)
Still nothing. Should I just assume that none of these cannons can actually be entered?
Now, I could head to world 6-6 over here next, but I can also start world 4 or 5 now. Which will it be? You guys vote on it and we'll find out next time!
Two 1-ups, 56 coins, and...
Man, that sucks. Well, I got five Yoshi coins, but there's still a sixth one that I know of...
To be continued...
Ow. Well, I was overdue for a silly mistake anyway. At least it wasn't fatal.
Thought I saw something above the midpoint, but I'm just imagining things...
Okay, that opens 6-6, but I want to see if I can find those Yoshi coins I missed in 6-5...
Radical.
Alright, now that I have Yoshi back, I'm not trapped in world 6 anymore.
Number three is also right in my path...
Hey, it looks like I can scroll away a few of the saws.
And there's the goal, but I can go down this pipe. I bet the remaining Yoshi coins are in here.
Nothing but a few coins and a lot of sharp stuff?
Ooh, looks tricky, but I've got a cape. I'm not worried. (It also helps that sprites don't "blackout" as well!)
Oh, this tricky jump again. Well, I made it last time, so there's no reason why I shouldn't be able to do it again!
Hmm... Well, I must've missed something. I'll figure it out after I play this bonus game.
FF>> while I pig out (?) on coins for a moment here...
Another DKC reference (but with coins instead of bananas again). I wonder which button I should use here...
Well, so much for that shell...
Hello!
Yes! I observed that it took about four game seconds between each firing, so that helped me nail it!
Oh, what's this? There was an extra 1-up hidden in the bonus game all this time? Neat.
DKC3 music this time. And cannons. (I'm not gonna have something shooting at me from the background or foreground, am I?)
Aha! What have we here?
No thanks. I don't need any run-of-the-mill mushrooms right now.
Ehh, normally I'd explore to the left and see what the bonus room skipped, but I'm a little pressed for time here...
A red buzzy. Now, I'm guessing this one actually is a spiny, unlike those purple buzzies in that other level.
Now, this looks like a real bonus room (even if there's lava)! A free 1-up, and tons of coins, including the missing Yoshi coins!
Whoa! This time it fired immediately, but fortunately, my cape spin worked on it!
Hello, and welcome back to Super SIG World 21! Now, before we look at the voting results, I'm going to replay this fortress to look for the Yoshi coin I missed.
Raise your hand if you thought I was gonna intentionally let Mario take a cannonball to the face there! (I considered it, though.)
Any other secrets? Who knows... I'm not going to spend forever and a half searching this room for them.
...the last Yoshi coin! Also, this serves as a way to skip a few hazards above.
Wait, there's three Yoshi coins in this room? But I also remember getting three in the main part of the level last time, so there's six total?
Okay, time's running out, so let's just rush through the rest of this room.
Yep, they're edible!
Okay, so knowing that the screen can scroll up, and the game gives me a feather here, what if I were to fly right here?
Well, there's no need to fight the boss again, so I'm outta here!
Oh, boy. This may be one of the most dangerous 1-up chance rooms I've entered.
Hmm... I wonder...
Okay, number one is right at the start...

1 vote for 6-S2, 1 vote for 6-66, 1 vote for me to glitch the map and get into level 0, 1 vote for Luigi to make a guest appearance, 1 vote for me to see if this factory makes any Italian rice, 1 vote for the first dungeon in Zelda: Ocarina of Time, 2 votes for 3-1, 3 votes for me to do 6-5 first, and 8 votes for me to do 6-S1 first! Alright, so let's head to that secret level!
That leads straight to the fortress, but there's still another exit to find there, and I bet I know where it is...
Now that's interesting. That poison mushroom block is invisible when the P-switch isn't active, but it can still be revealed.
And also, do you remember seeing this sign pointing to the left earlier? I do, and also the fact that this room even scrolls horizontally at all is another hint. Guess where I have to go!
There's number four, which is shortly after midpoint, but where could the last one be?
Alright, so which level should I play next? Let's take a look at the votes...
No thanks. I have my two feathers, so I don't need a flower now.
Whew. I wasn't sure how far away the goal was, since I didn't see any Yoshi coins...
Green ! blocks for everyone!
Oh, the screen can scroll up in this level. Also, that's only my second Yoshi coin? I passed midpoint a while ago.
I doubt fireballs will be extremely useful here...
Whoa! And I stumbled a bit there. I'm glad that cannon was late with its firing!
Parachuting bob-ombs, eh?
Yep, going right back through that room's entrance pipe does not lead to the same place as the other exit of that room. Instead, it leads to the green switch!
NOOOOO!!! YOSHIIIII!!! I only had you for about 45 seconds!
Hi, Yoshi! Can you last more than 45 seconds this time?
Ack! Didn't see that coming...
Okay, remember this dangerous bonus room down here that's hinted at by the purple coins?
Hey, Mario! Don't catch on the wall when I'm trying to spin jump! (At least that didn't get me killed or anything.)
Oh, that pipe is actually a big cannonball launcher (otherwise known as a cannon)! Oh, wait. I gotta check every pipe...
And I just get taken back here? Man, that "bonus" room sucked!
Oh, man. This jump looks really tricky...
There's Yoshi coin number three.
There's number two... Can't really miss it.
Still gotta check the pipes, and also let gold Bowser statues hop into pits.
I see those purple coins down there. Just like with similarly placed bananas in DKC, there's gotta be a secret there!
Interesting... Cape spinning the cannonballs makes them look like Bullet Bills as they die.
-Something- Something! Dotted green block something filled green block something. Something!?
And I still got the last two anyway!
But the lights don't just suddenly turn on and off like in DKC. They gradually fade in and out instead, and I really like that effect!
It can be cape spun like a spiny at least.
Made it, fortunately. Oh, I hope the goal is close by...
No thanks, I don't want any poison today... Huh?
Say... Could there be anything hidden down in this pit? I'm gonna check. (And I can Start+Select out if there's nothing.)
Also, this leads to 6-5. Guess where I'm heading next?
I'd rather have a second feather here, but I'll take this for now.
Oh, wow... It is indeed Blackout Basement this time!
I see the purple buzzies have made a reappearance.
Huzzah!
Yay! Hi, Yoshi! Glad to see you again! Hopefully I won't lose you within the next minute this time!
Oh, yeah. Gotta remember that Yoshi's immune to line-guided enemies, including these saws.
